  "copy": {
    "caption": "The fluffiest thing you'll ever almost catch.",
    "shortDescription": "Chinchillas come from the cold rocky mountains of South America, where their fur is so thick and dense — about sixty hairs growing from a single follicle — that fleas and other parasites can't even get through it. They don't bathe in water; they roll in special volcanic dust that absorbs oils and keeps their coat perfectly clean. Chinchillas can jump nearly two meters from a standing start. Fun fact: Chinchilla fur is the densest of any land mammal — it's twenty times softer than human hair."
